rom the cancer ward at Memorial Sloan-Kettering to New York City's gay club scene of the '80s, this poignant and authentic story takes us from underneath the dining room table to the stoop, the sidewalk, the street, and, ultimately, out into the wide world of immigration, gay subculture, cancer treatment, mental illness, gender dynamics, drug addiction, domestic violence, and a vast array of Italian American characters. With a quintessential New Yorker as narrator and guide, this journey crescendos in a reluctant return home to the timeless wisdom of a peasant, immigrant grandmother, Rosa Marsico Petruzzelli, who shows us the sweetest essence of soul.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aBronx (New York, N.Y.) -- Biography. 0aBronx (New York, N.Y.)vBiography. 0aItalian American lesbians -- New York (State) -- New York -- Biography. 0aItalian American lesbianszNew York (State)zNew YorkvBiography. 0aItalian Americans -- New York (State) -- New York -- Biography. 0aItalian AmericanszNew York (State)zNew YorkvBiography. 4aAmerican Studies : Italian American Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Lesbian / Gay Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Women's Studies. 4aGeneral Interest : Autobiography, Biography and Memoir. 4aGeneral Interest : Memoir. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Personal Memoirs.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143844527440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438445274423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438445274/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles